\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She pushes, tries to move. Hard as a statue.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Incredible.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She sways and moves and effortlessly glides. Admires Mandri.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 #}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I didn\u8217\'92t think it\u8217\'92d happen so soon. I\u8217\'92ve been waiting for a thousand years, and here you are.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri did not dare to speak but his muscles the scene and if he were to speak the tension break.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Tongue tied? Do I frighten you? I\u8217\'92m the mother of demons\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 who wouldn\u8217\'92t be scared of me?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Speak, Mandrameen. This is your moment.\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What is happening?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I can\u8217\'92t tell you. You can only be shown. You have to show yourself.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 #}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She pulls out a the black stone canvas and paints.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 #}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You want me to paint?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 #}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93That is what you were made for. That is why you are here. Why else would you have come to very doorstep of Shis? You will paint a self-portrait\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 the first }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 true}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  self-portrait you\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92ve ever painting..\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 #}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93But what is }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 happening}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 ?\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 #}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You have to move beyond that Mandri. Your mind is rooted in causes and effects, but none of these are real. You believe that you are Mandrameen, but that, too, is an illusion. Mandri was born, he will die, while your real being knows neither beginning, nor end.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri flick to Obo.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I can see I\u8217\'92m not making myself clear. Speech is too blunt a tool. If you begin to paint, I\u8217\'92m sure, you\u8217\'92ll come to understand.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93No.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93No?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m not going to do that.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Remembering what happened last time.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Disappointment.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 #}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Mandri, you are going to do it. Why else would you be here?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Upset confusion into a Beatific smile.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Remember Mandrameen the portrait painter? He knew what everyone looked like, except for himself. Isn\u8217\'92t that right? A true self-portrait is impossible because you don\u8217\'92t truly know your own face, even if you have a mirror\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 you can turn your head in every direction, but your eyes are always looking straight into themselves. You can look around and study your features, but you\u8217\'92ll never capture that look of looking away. That\u8217\'92s how the mirror nurtures the illusion of the self\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 you\u8217\'92re always looking straight into your own eyes and you begin to think that }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 that}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  is you. But you\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92ve never seen what you look like when you\u8217\'92re sleeping. You\u8217\'92ll never see what you look like when you\u8217\'92re dead. Everyone else\u8217\'92s eyes will shutter, but you\u8217\'92re own\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 you\u8217\'92ve never seen it happen, so who\u8217\'92s to say they\u8217\'92ll ever close? Do you blink, Mandri? Do you notice yourself blinking? Don\u8217\'92t blink now, or you might ruin it.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 #}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri realized he hadn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t yet blinked since. His eyes were stuck in the trance.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 #}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Do you sleep? What happens to Mandrameen when you sleep? Where does he go?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92ve never thought about it.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Sigh. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93At least you\u8217\'92re honest. That\u8217\'92s more than I can say for most people.\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Wistful look at Elrahet, Moto.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Look at them. They can\u8217\'92t see any of this. Look at how frightened they are of dying. You see, all they\u8217\'92ll lose is the stories they create of themselves. They invent themselves just to torment themselves.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Look to Obo.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93The Mazid too. What an ironic creature\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 spent its short life searching for freedom and finds it, but in so doing he\u8217\'92s become an enslaver of the Spark.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93How do you }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 know}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  that?\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92ll talk about him as I wish. You know it because Schisol told you?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I do.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri throws the rock.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Ack!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Stare at Mandri. Burst into an absolute fit of laughter.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Do you think you just proved me wrong!? You do, don\u8217\'92t you?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You\u8217\'92re so full of shit.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, my dear Mandri. How can you not see you\u8217\'92re the gaburshegee, the infertile ground, you deny everyone else\u8217\'92s plans for you, even mine. No one in the world can tell you what to do. But there\u8217\'92s one more person you have to reject.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Schisol?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yourself. You see through everyone else\u8217\'92s manipulations, you need only to take it one step further.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93And what if I don\u8217\'92t want to?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What you want is irrelevant.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Are you going to force me to paint a picture?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I cannot. You must pick up the brush on your own accord. When you\u8217\'92re ready. As you can see, we have all the time in the world.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 He\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d heard enough. Sees Obo\u8217\'92s spark interest.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Your Spark seeks another. This is what it wants.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You can be in union with it. This pain you feel, it is not necessary.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Sees Obo. Tearjerk. Injustice. Wasteful. Meaning.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I thought it was only Solraheen who\u8217\'92d make a sacrifice like this.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Solraheen a sacrifice!? You don\u8217\'92t actually believe that story, do you? You\u8217\'92re smarter than that, Mandri.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Confusion.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It was Schisol who called down the Fabled Black, not Solraheen. Schisol knew what would happen if the people were left to govern their own affairs. Given enough time, their selfishness, loneliness, and desperation would only strengthen in the absence of a god. Schisol trapped Himself to keep Solraheen from interfering with my work. And soon, when I am finished, and have united all the Spark, it is Schisol who will make the ultimate sacrifice\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 for dying is no great sacrifice, no, Schisol will live, He\u8217\'92ll live for all eternity alone, weeping, just to protect against the chance of His brother rising up and starting it all over again.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 #}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Where are you going?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93To test a theory.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Brings the Spark along, dragging the light of purpose along with him. Steps to the edge of the abyss.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What are you doing?\u8221\'94 Pell asked, her voice on as much of an edge as Mandri\u8217\'92s toes.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri answered her by dropping Obo\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s Spark. It fell into the Abyss, shining bright like a distant star, until finally, it disappeared all together, dragging a of million threads down with it.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 He blinked.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Time restarted and the . As cleared, there was Pell, fuming. She shrieked a , \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You\u8217\'92ll be back!\u8221\'94 she shrieked. \u8220\'93It is FATED!\u8221\'94. Her final word echoed through the cavernous void, and then she split into smoke. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri turned, and there was the Ayramun, }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What happened?\u8221\'94 Purl asked.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Let\u8217\'92s go,\u8221\'94 he replied. Brushed passed Moto who shouted, \u8220\'93Boy!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri turned and said defiantly, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93My name is Mandri.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Moto , sorry about it, before asking calmly, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What happened?\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Obo sacrificed himself for you.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93The Mazid?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93His name was Obo.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Kept on walking.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Mandri!\u8221\'94 Elrahet. \u8220\'93Can you see the threads of purpose?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yes. Not right now. But I could. Can you?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Nod.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You can see them right now?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I can.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93And where do they lead?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 #}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 #}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Let me make clear. From now on, I am no longer Elrahet. I am Elrah. You are now the Elrahun. Leave me on pain of death. Betray me on pain of a tortured life. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Sneer at them all.}
